attributes.value: Respects fair-dealing and fair-play
Values tradition
Finds the ideas of independence and freedom somewhat foolish
Considers craftsmanship to be relatively worthless
Deeply respects those that work hard at their labors
Is often cheerful
Is very slow to anger
Is very impolite and inconsiderate of propriety
Is quite ambitious
Is grateful when others help her out and tries to return favors
Presents herself modestly and frowns on any flashy accoutrements
Does not find most jokes humorous
Is completely convinced of her own worthlessness
Always acts with mercy and compassion at the forefront of her considerations
Is inattentive to detail in her own work
Can get caught up in internal deliberations when action is necessary
Only rarely tries to assert herself in conversation
Likes a little excitement now and then
Willpower
A meager kinesthetic sense
